reviews.review: I thought the movie was a good end to the Trilogy. I wasnt a huge fan of the past series. I just felt it was underwhelming, but was not disappointed either. A must see.
Lots of twists and turns and surprises. Want to go see it again!

To be brief: it's fan service heavy, doesn't explain how characters come back from the dead, stretches the force to unbelievable limits and doesn't explain it, doesn't explain ANYTHING really, has virtually no character development, it's inconsistent with all previous films, the ending negates the original trilogy's story arc which is NOT what you want to do, there are no consequential stakes, and the pacing is AWFUL. At this point, no reviewer or hardcore fan I know has said it was awesome, so it's just really disappointing. It makes me appreciate the prequels.

I will concede that it wasn't an amazing movie however, with that said, I loved the movie as I loved the whole franchise and it was great to see this nine-movie saga, which started the year that I was born, come to a finish in the only way it was meant to finish, good over evil...
Don’t listen to critics! First part was alright but from middle to end the fights were insane and the storyline brought satisfaction to a great era of storytelling
Simple. No surprises, no shocking scenes.

Episode IX is a fun movie to watch. But, is it a good Star Wars movie? Well. That depends on how much you KNOW about Star Wars lore. The less you know about Star Wars universe, the the more you will enjoy Episode 9. The reason is ignorance is bliss.
Nice closure had those 1977-80s happy feelings with super cool IMAX amazing video & sound!!!

Last Jedi was a NEGATIVE 2 (-2) for 5 stars, so comparing the two films this is an improvement.  This film tried to fix Luke’s character... But damage was done in the previous film... Also the handling of Rey’s character could have been done much better throughout the 3 movies... A very rushed film and the final battle was over so quickly... I don’t know why they could not make it better like the final battle in the revenge of sith... Overall since there is nothing else to watch in the theater it was ok because of visual effects... Star Wars shame on you, but on a positive note baby Yoda is on the Mandalorian
This movie was both frenetic and boring. Meh.
